--- &quot;Rakesh&quot; &lt;rakeshm@i...&gt; wrote:
&gt; I have a question on TestSuite.
&gt; Can we decide at run time, which test cases we want to include
&gt; in the TestSuite. Something like this
&gt;  
&gt; public class MyTestSuite extends Test 
&gt; {
&gt;     private static boolean required = false ;
&gt;     public static Test suite()
&gt;     {
&gt;         if( required )
&gt;         {
&gt;             suite.addTest(new TestSuite(TestCase1.class));
&gt;         }
&gt;         suite.addTest(new TestSuite(TestCase2.class));
&gt;         suite.addTest(new TestSuite(TestCase3.class));
&gt;     }
&gt; } 

In each of the test methods in TestCase1, you can say, at the start 
of the method:

| if (!SomeGlobalPlace.testsOfThisTypeShouldRun)
|     return;

Not pretty, but it can work.
